## Persistent Data Directory

`/data` is a persistent directory mounted from the host. Use it to cache downloaded
datasets, models, and other large files so they survive across runs:

```bash
# Example: download a dataset only if not already cached
if [ ! -d /data/my_dataset ]; then
    huggingface-cli download my-org/my-dataset --local-dir /data/my_dataset
fi
ln -s /data/my_dataset ./my_dataset  # symlink into your working dir
```

Always check `/data` before downloading anything large. Store HuggingFace datasets,
git-cloned repos, and pip wheels there when possible.

During literature review, actively search for existing implementations on GitHub and
Papers With Code. Clone relevant repos into `experiment_codebase/cloned_repos/` to study
and build on — don't write code from scratch when a reference implementation exists.
Start by creating `experiment_codebase/README.md` to document your experiment setup.

